<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Intel Corp.: The Santa Clara, Calif., producer of microcomputer chips said 1989 
full-year net income dropped 13.7% to $391 million, while revenue rose 9% to a 
record $3.1 billion. The firm blamed the closure of two of its oldest chip 
fabrication plants in part for the drop in earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
