</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rockwell International Corp.: First-quarter income fell 9% to $145.8 million 
from a year ago on sales of $2.9 billion, up about 3%. The El Segundo-based 
electronics and aerospace firm said results were affected by lower interest 
income and higher interest expense. Although its electronics businesses 
improved, earnings for its automotive segment were down substantially, the firm 
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
