<HEADLINE>
<P>
EARNINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Advanced Micro Devices: The Sunnyvale, Calif., integrated circuit maker said 
net income in fiscal 1989 totaled $46 million, more than double the $19 million 
of fiscal 1988. 
</P>
<P>
Sales were down 1.9% to $1.1 billion. The fiscal 1988 results included an 
unusual charge of $17.3 million associated with a work force reduction, closure 
of a manufacturing plant and other restructuring actions. The company said the 
increased earnings were due in part to driving unit costs down and an increase 
in international sales. 
</P>
</TEXT>
