</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Hilton Hotels Corp.: The hotel and casino firm posted net income for 1989 of 
$110.1 million, down 16% from the year before, on revenue of $998.2 million, up 
5% over 1988. Fourth-quarter net income for the Beverly Hills-based firm was 
$26.9 million, down 24% from the 1988 level, on revenue of $259.6 million, up 
2% over fourth-quarter 1988. The company said revenue from hotels rose 12%, 
while gaming revenue declined 20%. 
</P>
</TEXT>
