<P>
OIL WORKERS' STRIKE MAY AFFECT U.S. 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The country's 10 state-run oil refineries were expected to grind to a halt 
within 24 hours as union workers went on strike. 
</P>
<P>
Oil unions called the strike in support of a claim for a 64.8% pay raise to 
make up for inflation. The state-run oil company, Petrobras, offered 21.47%. 
The strike is likely to disrupt gasoline exports to the United States. Brazil 
is America's second-biggest foreign gasoline supplier. 
