<HEADLINE>
<P>
METRO DIGEST / LOCAL NEWS IN BRIEF: MOBIL OIL, EX-MANAGER CLEARED IN BLAST CASE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Mobil Oil and a former refinery executive were found innocent of criminal 
charges Tuesday that they obstructed a Torrance Fire Department investigation 
into a July 15, 1988, explosion that killed one man and injured two others. 
</P>
<P>
After Jesse Rodrigues, an assistant Torrance prosecutor, presented the city's 
case -- and without hearing any Mobil witnesses -- South Coast Municipal Judge 
Josh Fredricks decided that the city had not proved its case and entered a 
verdict of not guilty for Mobil and the now-retired executive, Thomas Gregory. 
In 1988, he was the second-ranking manager at the Torrance refinery. 
</P>
<P>
"We're pleased with the way this thing went," said Mobil spokesman Jim 
Carbonetti. 
</P>
