<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROUNDUP 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In other boys' basketball games: 
</P>
<P>
Canyon 60, Palmdale 59 -- Canyon trailed 54-43 with three and a half minutes to 
play and by seven points with a minute and a half left but pulled out the 
victory when Jermaine Nixon hit a three-point shot from the left wing with 
three seconds left at Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Nixon had tied the Golden League game, 57-57, on a layup with 29 seconds 
remaining. He led Canyon (13-5, 2-2) with 14 points. Lance Moore scored 12 and 
had eight assists for Canyon. 
</P>
<P>
Hart 87, Burbank 71 -- Hart outscored Burbank, 24-11, in the fourth quarter of 
a Foothill League game at Hart. 
</P>
<P>
Hart center Chad Fotheringham led all scorers with 25 points and also made six 
steals. Paul Tapp led Burbank with 21 points. 
</P>
<P>
Alemany 45, St. Francis 43 -- Tim Fontanette scored a team-high 15 points in a 
Del Rel League game at Alemany. 
</P>
<P>
Rich Dice added 10 points for Alemany (7-12, 1-2). Matt Vitti scored a 
game-high 17 points for St. Francis. 
</P>
<P>
Antelope Valley 71, Ridgecrest Burroughs 45 -- Chris Walters scored 21 points 
-- all in the first half -- as Antelope Valley (16-3, 4-0) cruised to a Golden 
League win at Ridgecrest. 
</P>
<P>
Brock Chase and Jabbar Briggs each scored 14 points for the Antelopes, who led, 
15-12, at halftime. 
</P>
<P>
Crescenta Valley 61, Glendale 42 -- Senior guard Mike Johnson scored 16 points 
to lead Crescenta Valley in a Pacific League game at home. Crescenta Valley 
(11-6, 3-1) outscored Glendale, 19-4, in the third quarter. 
</P>
<P>
Pasadena 82, Hoover 56 -- John Worden led Hoover with 15 points in a Pacific 
League game at Hoover. John Hillman and Dave Ulloa scored 13 and 10 points for 
Hoover. 
</P>
<P>
GIRLS' BASKETBALL 
</P>
<P>
Thousand Oaks 68, Simi Valley 60 -- Michelle Palmisano scored 31 points for 
Thousand Oaks in a Marmonte League victory at Simi Valley. It was the third 
game in a row in which the sophomore guard had scored more than 30. 
</P>
<P>
Erinn Clark came off the bench to score 18 for Thousand Oaks (9-9, 2-3), and 
Suzanne Nelinger scored 12. Simi Valley's Tammy Pacheco scored 19 points. 
</P>
<P>
BOYS' SOCCER 
</P>
<P>
Royal 4, Channel Islands 1 -- Matt Brinkman scored two first-half goals for 
Royal in a Marmonte League match at Royal (15-2-1, 5-0). 
</P>
<P>
