<HEADLINE>
<P>
ARGENTINA TO PLAY MEXICO AT COLISEUM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Argentina, the defending World Cup soccer champion which has yet to win after 
two exhibition games this year, will play Mexico tonight at 8 in the Coliseum. 
</P>
<P>
Most of the players who will represent Argentina in this summer's World Cup in 
Italy are expected to be with the team tonight, a notable exception being Diego 
Maradona, star of the championship team. He is under contract to Napoli in the 
Italian League. 
</P>
<P>
Argentina earlier lost to Monaco, 2-0, and played to a scoreless tie with 
Guatemala. 
</P>
<P>
Mexico is expected to field a young team as it builds for the future. It was 
disqualified from this year's World Cup for using over-age players in a junior 
tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
