<TEXT>
<P>
Gillette Wins Round in Court: U.S. District Judge Thomas Hogan denied a Justice 
Department request to immediately freeze Gillette Co.'s planned acquisition of 
part of Wilkinson Sword's international razor blade business. The judge refused 
to issue a temporary restraining order, saying Gillette has stated that no 
action would be taken without a 10-day advance notice to the government. The 
acquisition is being challenged on anti-competitive grounds, alleging a 
violation of the Clayton Act. 
</P>
