<P>
Subaru Parent to Build U.S. Engine Plant: Japan's Fuji Heavy Industries Ltd., 
maker of Subaru cars, plans to build an engine plant in the United States, a 
spokesman said. At the same time, Fuji said it has offered to acquire all 
Subaru of America Inc. shares it does not already own for $6 each, or about 
$144 million. Fuji now owns about 49.6% of the U.S. marketing unit for Subaru 
cars. 
</P>
