</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
T-Bill Rates Rise: The Treasury sold $7.6 billion of new three-month bills at 
an average discount rate of 7.68%, up from 7.57% last week. 
</P>
<P>
Another $7.6 billion of new six-month bills was sold at an average discount 
rate of 7.54%, up from 7.44% last week. The rates were the highest since Dec. 
26. The new discount rates understate the actual return to investors -- 7.94% 
for three-month bills, with a $10,000 bill selling for $9,805.90 and 7.95% for 
a six-month bill selling for $9,618.80. The discount rate reflects the price 
discount received when government securities are purchased at less than their 
face value. 
</P>
</TEXT>
