<P>
Paul Cook, founder of Raychem Corp., Menlo Park, will retire April 1 as chief 
executive along with Robert Halperin, president and chief operating officer. 
</P>
<P>
Stepping up from senior vice president to the positions of both chief executive 
and president will be Robert Saldich, 56. Cook, 65, will remain chairman, and 
Halperin, 61, will become vice chairman. He also will remain as chairman of the 
company's Raynet subsidiary. Raychem makes plastic and metal products. 
</P>
