</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOT GUNS: No one wants to talk about it officially but Orange County Sheriff's 
Department investigators are scrambling to explain an embarrassing theft of 
guns from their training academy in Orange. . . . The heist, which one source 
said involved as many as 42 handguns, took place about two weeks ago. Then, 
sources say, at least four people were arrested in a bust that took place 
shortly before midnight last Wednesday at the Best Western Stardust Motel in 
Anaheim. . . . Next step: sheriff's officials meet this morning to determine 
the status of the investigation. Steve Emmons and Mark I. Pinsky 
