<HEADLINE>
<P>
SEA VIEW LEAGUE GIRLS' BASKETBALL ROUNDUP; 
</P>
<P>
EVEN WITHOUT EARLE, ESTANCIA BREEZES PAST NEWPORT HARBOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By DONNA CARTER, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The Estancia High School girls' basketball team ended its two-game Sea View 
League losing streak with a 63-43 victory over Newport Harbor Tuesday night at 
Newport Harbor. 
</P>
<P>
Without leading scorer and point guard Melody Earle, the Eagles (7-8, 1-2) 
struggled while losing to University and Saddleback. Earle chipped a bone in 
her left ankle in the opening round of the Marina Tournament. But she continued 
to limp through several games before sitting out the first two league games on 
the advice of her doctor, Estancia Coach Lisa McNamee said. 
</P>
<P>
Tuesday night the Eagles again looked as if they would struggle without Earle's 
18 points a game, but Estancia outscored Newport Harbor, 26-11, in the fourth 
quarter to turn a close game into a rout. 
</P>
<P>
Estancia took advantage of the boards and the Sailors' 30 turnovers with 
Monique Sweet pushing the ball up court for easy transition baskets. 
</P>
<P>
"We haven't been able to get rolling without Melody," Estancia Coach Lisa 
McNamee said. "Tonight we had other people respond offensively." 
</P>
<P>
Those other people were sophomore Sweet and senior Liz Collins. Sweet, who had 
been averaging 14 points, stepped up her offensive production. She led all 
scorers with 26 points. Collins responded on the boards grabbing 19 rebounds 
and scoring 12 points. Estancia continually scored second-chance baskets when 
Sweet wasn't pushing the ball up court, but the real key was defense. 
</P>
<P>
"I told them at halftime that Stacey Giem was getting a little bit frustrated 
on offense, and she basically is their offense," McNamee said. "No doubt about 
it, Patrice (Lumpkin) holding her down was the key to the game." 
</P>
<P>
Lumpkin scored 15 points and held Giem to 16. Jenni Hall added 13 for Newport 
Harbor (5-8, 1-2). 
</P>
<P>
Estancia led, 41-38, with five minutes to play when Sailor point guard Alison 
Izumita left the game with her fifth foul. Collins sank both free throws, 
Lumpkin added a basket and Sweet, who was fouled, made her first free throw. 
She missed her second but Collins' follow was good for a three-point play that 
put Estancia firmly in front, 48-38. 
</P>
<P>
In other Sea View games: 
</P>
<P>
University 44, Saddleback 30 -- Senior forward Denise Gandara scored 25 points 
and had 11 rebounds to lead University (12-4, 2-1). Sophomore center Tara Wolff 
had eight points, a career-high 20 rebounds and six blocked shots. 
</P>
<P>
Tustin 66, Corona del Mar 29 -- Christine Garner had 21 points and Nancy Vinh 
had 12 as Tustin (14-5, 3-0) outscored host Corona del Mar 24-1 in the fourth 
quarter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
