<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ron Kovic, anti-war activist and subject of the current film "Born on the 
Fourth of July," and the film's Academy Award-winning director, Oliver Stone, 
will speak at UC Irvine Feb. 7 at 8 p.m. Each will speak for about 30 minutes 
about their own experiences in Vietnam, the making of the film, and the film 
industry's representation of the Cold War. 
</P>
<P>
A panel discussion will include Times reporter and author Robert Scheer. The 
seminar, titled "Vietnam: The Making of 'Born on the Fourth of July,' " is 
being sponsored by UCI's Global Peace and Conflict Studies program and will be 
held in the Science Lecture Hall. Tickets are $2 and must be purchased in 
advance. Information: (714) 856-5000. 
</P>
