<TEXT>
<P>
President Bush sent a senior foreign policy adviser to the Philippines today to 
underscore support for President Corazon Aquino amid fears of a new coup 
attempt against her government. 
</P>
<P>
Robert Gates, Bush's deputy national security adviser, left Washington around 
midnight and was to hold talks with Aquino on Thursday. He also will confer 
with Fidel Ramos, the Philippine defense secretary. 
</P>
