<P>
JUDGE FINES WINFIELD IN DIVORCE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
<P>
HOUSTON 
</P>
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
A judge has fined New York Yankees outfielder Dave Winfield $10,000 for failing 
to disclose a California bank account during the pretrial phase of divorce 
proceedings from his common-law wife. 
</P>
<P>
A jury last summer found that Winfield had a common-law marriage to flight 
attendant Sandra Renfro from 1982 to 1985, and a judge ordered him to pay 
temporary alimony and child support for the couple's daughter. 
</P>
<P>
State District Judge Allen Daggett Tuesday postponed the Winfield-Renfro 
divorce hearing until the issue of the California bank account is settled. 
Winfield holds the joint account with his current wife, Tonya. 
</P>
<P>
Daggett ordered Winfield to submit all documentation pertaining to the account 
to Renfro's attorney, Earle Lilly. The judge also sanctioned Winfield to pay 
Renfro $10,000. 
</P>
